  "body": "/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nCreate a job that will fail many times, but eventually succeeds.\r\n\r\nAfter the job's pod succeeds, it takes a long time to update the job status.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nAfter the job's pod succeeds, the job's status is updated immediately.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nCreate a simple configmap:\r\n```\r\napiVersion: v1\r\nkind: ConfigMap\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: result\r\ndata:\r\n  result: failure\r\n```\r\n\r\nCreate a job that runs a pod that fails based on the value of the configmap:\r\n```\r\napiVersion: batch/v1\r\nkind: Job\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: testjob\r\nspec:\r\n  backoffLimit: 100\r\n  completions: 1\r\n  parallelism: 1\r\n  template:\r\n    spec:\r\n      restartPolicy: Never\r\n      containers:\r\n      - command:\r\n        - sh\r\n        - -c\r\n        - if [ \"${RESULT}\" = \"failure\" ]; then exit 1; fi\r\n        image: busybox\r\n        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent\r\n        name: testjob\r\n        env:\r\n        - name: RESULT\r\n          valueFrom:\r\n            configMapKeyRef:\r\n              name: result\r\n              key: result\r\n```\r\n\r\nLet the job fail a few times\r\nAfter about a minute or so, edit the configmap and change the value of its `result` key:\r\n\r\n```\r\nkubectl edit cm/result\r\n```\r\n\r\nWait for the job to launch a pod that succeeds\r\n```\r\nkubectl get pods -w\r\n```\r\n\r\nWait for the job to be updated based on the success of the pod\r\n```\r\nkubectl get jobs -w\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere is about a 5 min wait between the time the pod succeeds and the job's status is updated.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\nThe job controller immediately gets a pod updated event, which results in the `enqueueController` method getting called.\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/controller/job/job_controller.go#L263\r\n\r\nThe `enqueueController` method applies a backoff based on how many times the job has been retried:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/controller/job/job_controller.go#L352-L361\r\n\r\nThis seems wrong. The backoff should be applied to pod creation and not to handling an update event from an existing pod.",
